          h1 FOOD BANK 

          p Each year CCCC distributes over 15,000 food boxes with enough food to feed over 50,000 adults and children. Persons needing emergency food are referred by a variety of agencies but primarily by the CAP (Community Action Program) office. Other referrals come from Child Protective Services, non profits, churches, schools, the Chandler Police Department’s Victim Services and the Chandler Fire Department.

          h3 Emergency Food Boxes 

          p Tailored to family size and special dietary needs including infants, children, and homeless individuals.

          h3 Emergency Food Distribution:

          p Monday – 12:00 through 3:00 pm

          p Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday – 9:00 through 12:00 pm

          h3 Supplemental Food Boxes

          p Distributed weekly containing fresh perishable food

          h3 Supplemental Food Distribution:

          p Every Friday – 9:00 through 11:00

          h3 Food Donations 

          p Food is donated from local grocers and restaurants, individuals, clubs, businesses, faith organizations and more. Federal food comes through the United Food Bank. All donations are accepted during business hours. Please contact the office for special arrangements.

          p *In accordance with Federal law and U.S Department of Agriculture policy, this institution is prohibited from discriminating on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, age, or disability.
        .col-sm-8.col-sm-offset-2.main-content(ng-show="page.isSelected(2)")
          h1 FAMILY RESOURCE CENTER
          h3 Family Resource Center Activities

          p The Family Resource Center provides a safe, positive environment for family development. Their model is to meet some of the needs families have outside of nutritional.

          h3 Giggles Squiggles and Squirms:

          p Early Literacy Program 3-5 Year Olds – Monday & Thursday between 1:00 and 3:00 pm

          h3 Interactive Family Play:

          p Call for an open time for just your family or join us every Friday between 8:30 and 10:00 am

          h3 Baby Brain Box:

          p New Directions Institute – Getting Your Child’s Brain Ready for School; please call for more information or to schedule an appointment.

          h3 Weekend Homeless Meal Program:

          p Touch of Love Ministries -Fellowship meal open to any and all on the last Saturday of the month – November 24th between 3:00 and 5:00 pm.

          h3 Free Fluoride Treatments:

          p Dignity Health – children ages 0-5 during supplemental food distribution – November 30th between 7:30 and 10:00 am.

          h3 Narcotics Anonymous:

          p Meetings are every Wednesday, Friday, and Sunday at 7:00 pm.


